items.name: d20 NPC Wiki
items.title: d20 NPC Wiki
items.headline: Roll over to the d20 NPCs Wiki!
items.desc:
The d20 NPCs Wiki is the resource and repository for game masters, sporting an army of NPCs to bolster your encounters!

This Wiki is intended as a resource for the poor, harried game master and serves as a repository for NPCs and monsters of all kinds. If you are using the NPCs and monsters here, please consider adding some contributions of your own so that the Wiki can continue to grow!

items.name: Comic Book Series
items.title: Comic Book Series
items.headline: Welcome to the Comic Book Series Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Comic Book Series Wiki. The goal of this Wiki is to introduce you to on-going comic book series that you might have trouble understanding if you were to just go into a shop and pick up the latest issue.

items.name: Cognitive Linguistics
items.title: Cognitive Linguistics
items.headline: Cognitive Linguistics Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the new Free Encyclopedia of Cognitive Linguistics and Related Disciplines. Cognitive linguistics is a branch of linguistics; it interprets language in terms of the concepts. The goal of this wiki is to serve as a comprehensive encyclopedia on Cognitive Linguistics and related disciplines.

items.name: CSI
items.title: CSI
items.headline: CSI: Crime Scene Investigation Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to CSI: Wiki! We strive to document everything there is to know about the iconic TV franchise, from its inception to its latest incarnations. Are you a CSI fan? Then this is the site for you! Join us and share your knowledge and passion about all things CSI. After all, this is a community site that anyone can edit, including you!

items.name: Image Comics Database
items.title: Image Comics Database
items.headline: Welcome to the Image Comics Wiki
items.desc:
Image is a comics and graphic novels publisher formed in 1992 by seven of Marvel Comics’ best-selling artists. Since that time, Image has gone on to become the third largest comics publisher in the United States.

The wiki is a database of all things Image related, including information on some of the more recognizable comics like Spawn and Witchblade.

items.name: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.title: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.headline: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.desc: Cardcaptor Sakura is an award-winning magical girl manga series first published in Japan. From the manga to the television series and more, we here at the Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki document everything there is to know about the series. As a Wikia site, anyone can edit, including you, so join us and share your knowledge and passion for Cardcaptor Sakura!

items.name: Fallout Wiki
items.title: Fallout Wiki
items.headline: Nukapedia - The Fallout Wiki
items.desc: Created and maintained by the Fallout community, Nukapedia: The Fallout Wiki aims to create the best resource for the Fallout series of games, including, but not limited to: Fallout, Fallout 2, Fallout 3, Fallout: New Vegas, Fallout 4, Fallout 76, Fallout: Tactics, Fallout: Brotherhood of Steel and Van Buren.

items.name: Marvel Fanon
items.title: Marvel Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to Marvel Fanon Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to Marvel Fanon Wikia! The Marvel Fanon Wikia is a site for all fans of Marvel who also love writing fan fiction! Enter now to create your own story or to collaborate with other authors in writing an original Marvel fan fiction! Check out the Marvel Fanon Wikia and find out how you can contribute!

items.name: Animaniacs Wiki
items.title: Animaniacs Wiki
items.headline: We're the Animaniacs ... Wiki!
items.desc:
Hellooooooo Nurse! You've just jumped from the water tower and into Animaniacs Wiki, the wiki devoted to the award-winning series Animaniacs! Faboo!

Read all about the manic adventures of Yakko, Wakko, and Dot Warner, or delve into the other segments such as Pinky and the Brain or the Goodfeathers!

items.name: Olympics Wiki
items.title: Olympics Wiki
items.headline: Olympics Wiki
items.desc: Olympics Wiki is a community of editors, athletes, sports fans, students, and others dedicated to preserving and spreading information having to do with various Olympic games throughout history. In addition to creating a comprehensive Olympics site unlike any other, Olympics Wiki strives to generate excitement about the upcoming summer and winter games and highlight feature stories and spotlight athletes.

items.name: Long Island Music Scene Wiki
items.title: Long Island Music Scene Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Long Island Music Scene Wikia
items.desc:
The wiki about the history of the Long Island Music Scene that anyone can edit.

Wikia is a website that hosts User Generated Communities that can revolve around many different genres, including entertainment, video games, and lifestyle.  Everyone is invited to participate and edit, and anyone can create their very ow wiki about the topic of their choice.

items.name: Public Safety Wiki
items.title: Public Safety Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Public Safety Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Public Safety Wiki! This wiki is a source of information for those curious about public safety and the organizations related to the topic. The Public Safety Wiki contains references, tips, alerts, and more for anyone interested in learning more about the importance of public safety. Enter now to browse and contribute to the wiki!

items.name: FicSpecies
items.title: FicSpecies
items.desc: FicSpecies is a comprehensive bestiary of the creatures, races and beings that populate the wonderful world of fiction, including monsters, aliens, fantasy races and much more. Our purposefully loose definition of "fiction" includes everything from film and television, literature, manga and anime, comic books and video games to mythology and folklore, cryptozoology and popular culture.

items.name: The Magic School Bus Wiki
items.title: The Magic School Bus Wiki
items.headline: Enroll in the Magic School Bus Wiki!
items.desc:
Magic School Bus Wiki is a collaborative online encyclopedia dedicated to the popular Magic School Bus franchise.

The Magic School Bus is a series of children's books about science. They feature the antics of Ms. Frizzle, an elementary school teacher, and her class of eight children (in the original books, the class population was at a larger and more standard amount), who board a magical school bus which takes them on field trips into the solar system, under the Bed, into the American Flag, or to other such impossible locations. The books are written in the first person from the point of view of an unnamed student in "the Friz's" class. The class pet, Liz, a lizard, accompanied the class on their field trips.

items.name: UK Politics Wiki
items.title: UK Politics Wiki
items.desc: UK Politics Wiki - does what it says on the tin. We are a wiki committed to coverage of all aspects of UK Politics, from the days of Tories and Whigs, right up to Brexit and the implications of Trump. We have articles on previous Prime Ministers as well as articles updated daily about current affairs.

items.headline: Czech Star Wars Wiki
items.desc: Největší česká internetová encyklopedie o Star Wars.

items.name: Cryptipedia
items.title: Cryptipedia
items.headline: Welcome to Cryptipedia
items.desc: Welcome to Cryptipedia, the wiki all about cryptics and anything related to the topic including tips to solve them! Cryptics or a cryptic crossword will typically have difficult clues that indicate the solutions indirectly. Enter Cryptipedia now to learn more about them, the different indicators, and much, much more!

items.name: Athlepedia, The Athletics Wiki
items.title: Athlepedia, The Athletics Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Athlepedia
items.desc:
This site is about physical fitness and health.

Don't let the term mislead you -- elite, in the case, has a double meaning. We're talking about the pursuit of excellence, not just in fitness but in knowledge. Elite knowledge of fitness, gleaned from these pages, will help you propel yourself to success faster than normal, however, the reality is that wisdom means nothing without application. So we challenge you to go out and play -- get out and turn up the dial. Make it happen.

items.name: Vocaloid Lyrics Wiki
items.title: Vocaloid Lyrics Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Vocaloid Lyrics Wiki!
items.desc: Vocaloid Lyrics Wiki is a collaborative website for the purpose of presenting VOCALOID original songs. If you want to create an article, please see the Song Article Guideline for further guidance. Also note that not all fan translations are accepted to be featured in this wiki; they must meet certain conditions as explained in the Policy page.

items.name: Chrome Shelled Regios Wiki
items.title: Chrome Shelled Regios Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Chrome Shelled Regios wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to Chrome Shelled Regios Wiki! Chrome Shelled Regios (鋼殻のレギオス) is a Japanese light novel series written by Shūsuke Amagi and illustrated by Miyū. An anime adaptation was produced by Zexcs and aired from January 11, 2009 to June 20, 2009. It is licensed in North America by Funimation Entertainment.

items.name: UK Comics Wiki
items.title: UK Comics Wiki
items.headline: Discover the UK Comics Wikia
items.desc: Fans of comics rejoice - the UK Comics Wikia is a Wikia community that was founded by fans of  British comics. The UK Comics community sets on compiling information about the writers, the comic strips, the artists, and anything else that makes up the British comic scene. We are always looking for new fans and contributors.

items.name: WikiaParoles
items.title: WikiaParoles
items.headline: WikiaParoles donne le la
items.desc:
WikiaParoles a été le premier site francophone à proposer légalement les paroles des chansons françaises sur Internet, grâce à un contrat de licence entre Gracenotes et Wikia.

Le wiki ne contient que l'essentiel : les paroles et les listes de chansons par artiste. Vous pouvez y participer, ajouter/corriger des textes, etc.

items.name: Loonatics Unleashed Wiki
items.title: Loonatics Unleashed Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Loonatics Unleashed Wikia!
items.desc: Welcome to the Loonatics Unleashed Wikia! Here you can discuss and expand all you're knowledge on the Loonatics. We are a public community and anybody can edit our articles, however please remember to ensure a neat and informative website. We also encourage editors to create a registered account so that you will be easier to contact and identify. If you have any questions, concerns, or suggestions please contact an administrator. Make sure to check out the characters and episodes section!

items.title: DC Comics Extended Universe Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about the Man of Steel film in the DC Cinematic Universe Wiki!
items.desc: The DC Cinematic Universe focuses on the film series started by the film Man of Steel. Find out more about the film in this wiki and discover more about Superman's origin. Learn how he became Superman and how he got his super powers. Learn more of about the films the films that will be in the franchise soon like The Batman, Wonder Woman, The Flash, the sequel to Man of Steel, and the Justice Leage movie.
